2026-03-20T20:19:40.616Z JOY-0010 item.created "Rethink tutorial format for readability" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-20T20:19:48.629Z JOY-0010 comment.added "Current tutorial uses a man-page-inspired plaintext format. Issues: (1) renders poorly on GitHub (no markdown formatting), (2) not pleasant in a text editor, (3) lacks color/highlighting even in terminal compared to modern colored man pages. Consider: Markdown for GitHub/editor readability, or a proper man page with troff/mdoc for terminal rendering, or both (Markdown source, generate man page from it). The tutorial is shown via 'joy tutorial' so the CLI could render Markdown with terminal formatting." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
