2026-03-20T20:38:37.184Z JOY-000A comment.added "All three parts resolved: (1) joy init writes full defaults to config.defaults.yaml (JOY-000F). (2) Code fallback via layered config -- joy config get always returns a value for known keys (agents struct added). (3) Auto-update not needed -- new code defaults are automatically visible through the merge chain without touching config files." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-20T20:38:37.187Z JOY-000A item.status_changed "new -> closed" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-20T20:41:54.462Z JOY-0003 item.updated "Validate keys in joy config set/get, reject unknown" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-20T20:42:00.174Z JOY-0003 comment.added "With config layering (JOY-000F), config.yaml is personal and gitignored. Unknown keys only affect the user who sets them. AI tools read specific keys, not the full config. Risk via config.defaults.yaml (committed) exists but is a code review concern. Lowered to low priority." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-20T20:44:55.769Z JOY-0003 comment.added "Closed in favor of a broader prompt injection idea. Key validation alone does not address the real concern -- any Joy data (items, comments, config) could contain manipulative text for AI tools." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-20T20:44:55.772Z JOY-0003 item.status_changed "new -> closed" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-20T20:45:01.277Z JOY-0011 item.created "Prompt injection resilience for AI-facing Joy data" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-20T20:45:13.868Z JOY-0011 comment.added "AI tools read Joy data via CLI output (joy config, joy show, joy ls). Any text field -- item titles, descriptions, comments, config values -- could contain instructions that manipulate AI behavior. This is not Joy-specific (all tools feeding text to LLMs face this), but Joy should consider what it can do on its side. Possible approaches: (1) sanitize output when consumed by AI tools (detect agent context), (2) separate trusted (project owner) from untrusted (contributor) data, (3) document the risk and recommend code review for config.defaults.yaml and item content. Originated from JOY-0003 discussion." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-20T20:47:33.441Z JOY-0001 comment.added "Already implemented -- joy init shows 'Using AI tools? Run joy ai setup to configure integration.' at the end." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
